*splashutils-1.5.4.4-r12 (18 Nov 2013)

  18 Nov 2013; Vincent Strubel <clipos@ssi.gouv.fr>
  +splashutils-1.5.4.4-r12.ebuild, -splashutils-1.5.4.4-r11.ebuild,
  files/splashutils-1.5.4.4-clip.patch:
  Bump libpng distfile.
  Remove dependency on fbgrab for CLIP (only useful for taking
  screenshots).
  Restore accented characters in boot msg (they only needed to be
  switched to UTF-8).

*splashutils-1.5.4.4-r11 (18 Oct 2013)

  18 Oct 2013; Vincent Strubel <clipos@ssi.gouv.fr>
  +splashutils-1.5.4.4-r11.ebuild, -splashutils-1.5.4.4-r10.ebuild,
  files/splash:
  Add 'splash exit' command.

*splashutils-1.5.4.4-r10 (14 Oct 2013)

  14 Oct 2013; Vincent Strubel <clipos@ssi.gouv.fr>
  +splashutils-1.5.4.4-r10.ebuild, -splashutils-1.5.4.4-r9.ebuild,
  +files/splashutils-1.5.4.4-clip-openrc.patch,
  +files/splashutils-1.5.4.4-multi-keyboard.patch:
  Bump to latest rev from gentoo.
  Remove splashutils-functions-bl1.sh now that we've switched to openrc.
  Add a clip patch to make the openrc splash plugin stop fbsplash at
  the end of the default runlevel, rather than the boot runlevel : the
  vanilla behaviour of the plugin is to stop as soon as a runlevel other
  than 'boot' is finished, but in CLIP's case this means splash stops
  at the end of the 'nonetwork' runlevel, while we still have 'default'
  to run. Change this to only exit when the 'default' runlevel is done.

*splashutils-1.5.4.4-r9 (11 Oct 2013)

  11 Oct 2013; Vincent Strubel <clipos@ssi.gouv.fr>
  +splashutils-1.5.4.4-r9.ebuild, -splashutils-1.5.4.4-r8.ebuild,
  files/splashutils-1.5.4.4-clip.patch:
  Remove accents from boot messages for now, since they don't 
  work too well with openrc.
  Remove a call to '/bin/sed -i <> /etc/mtab' which on CLIP is :
   - useless (no stale lines in mtab, which is a symlink to /proc/mounts)
   - annoying (creates a sed warning)
   - dangerous (might result in turning /etc/mtab into an actual file
     if / is mounted R/W).

